# Trivy ignore list — security-trivy workflow.
#
# Findings grouped by architectural category with shared reasoning
# blocks. Per-CVE notes only when CVE-specific context is needed
# beyond the category reasoning. PR-C's PR description has the
# full triage walkthrough.
#
# Each category's reasoning includes revisit triggers — conditions
# under which the category-level disposition should be reconsidered.
# Trivy applies ignores globally by CVE ID; a CVE appearing in
# multiple images is listed once in the most-specific category.


# ===========================================================================
# Category A: Base image CVEs, no upstream fix or will-not-fix
# ===========================================================================
#
# Findings in Debian base packages where either no fix exists yet
# (status: `affected`) or upstream maintainers decided not to patch
# (status: `will_not_fix`). Accepted at portfolio scope: single-tenant,
# low blast radius, no exploit path identified through Ironforge's
# request surface (ncurses is not loaded by the portal Lambda runtime;
# zlib MiniZip overflow requires attacker-controlled ZIP input which
# the portal doesn't process).
#
# Revisit triggers:
#   (a) Upstream publishes a fix (status changes `affected` → `fixed`);
#       move the CVE to Category B.
#   (b) Multi-tenant or compliance scope arrives that doesn't accept
#       residual risk on these CVEs.
#   (c) Active-exploitation advisory specifically for one of these
#       CVEs.

CVE-2025-69720  # libtinfo6 / ncurses-base / ncurses-bin — buffer overflow, no fix
CVE-2023-45853  # zlib1g — MiniZip integer overflow, upstream will-not-fix


# ===========================================================================
# Category B: Debian base CVEs, fix available — accept floating-tag lag
# ===========================================================================
#
# Findings with upstream fixes available in newer Debian package
# revisions. `apps/web/Dockerfile` pulls the floating tag
# `node:22-bookworm-slim` (and its `public.ecr.aws/docker/library/`
# mirror), so security updates land automatically when Docker Hub
# republishes the tag — typically within days of CVE publication.
# The current scan reflects the lag between fix publication and tag
# refresh.
#
# Revisit triggers:
#   (a) The lag exceeds 30 days from CVE publication; consider pinning
#       to a specific Node 22 patch version with the fix included.
#   (b) An audit framework requires demonstrating active patching
#       rather than passive floating-tag updates.
#   (c) Active-exploitation advisory on one of these CVEs.

CVE-2026-33845  # libgnutls30 — fix: 3.7.9-2+deb12u7
CVE-2026-42010  # libgnutls30 — fix: 3.7.9-2+deb12u7
CVE-2026-33846  # libgnutls30 — fix: 3.7.9-2+deb12u7
CVE-2026-3833   # libgnutls30 — fix: 3.7.9-2+deb12u7
CVE-2026-42009  # libgnutls30 — fix: 3.7.9-2+deb12u7
CVE-2026-33671  # picomatch (bundled in Node base) — fix: 4.0.4 / 3.0.2 / 2.3.2


# ===========================================================================
# Category C: AWS Lambda runtime base CVEs, AWS-managed refresh
# ===========================================================================
#
# Findings in JavaScript packages bundled by the AWS Lambda team in
# `public.ecr.aws/lambda/nodejs:22` — the runtime base for the
# run-terraform Lambda (per ADR-009 § Amendments / PR-C.6). We don't
# control these dependencies; AWS Lambda publishes the base with their
# chosen versions. The run-terraform Dockerfile pulls the floating
# `nodejs:22` tag so AWS refreshes land automatically.
#
# Revisit triggers:
#   (a) The lag exceeds 60 days from CVE publication; open an AWS
#       support ticket or evaluate moving to a self-managed base
#       (significant work — abandons the Lambda-blessed runtime
#       interface pattern).
#   (b) Active-exploitation advisory on one of these CVEs.

CVE-2026-42033  # axios — fix: 1.15.1 / 0.31.1 (AWS Lambda Node 22 base)
CVE-2026-42035  # axios — fix: 1.15.1 / 0.31.1 (AWS Lambda Node 22 base)
CVE-2026-42043  # axios — fix: 1.15.1 / 0.31.1 (AWS Lambda Node 22 base)
CVE-2026-42264  # axios — fix: 1.15.2 (AWS Lambda Node 22 base)
CVE-2026-44665  # fast-xml-builder — fix: 1.1.7 (AWS Lambda Node 22 base)
